2.20	John_McCluskey,_Baron_McCluskey	John McCluskey, Baron McCluskey	John Herbert McCluskey, Baron McCluskey (born 12 June 1929) is a Scottish lawyer, judge and politician, who served as Solicitor General for Scotland, the country's junior Law Officer from 1974 to 1979, and as a Senator of the College of Justice, a judge of Scotland's Supreme Courts, from 1984 to 2004.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Royal_Coat_of_Arms_of_the_United_Kingdom_%28Scotland%29.svg/150px-Royal_Coat_of_Arms_of_the_United_Kingdom_%28Scotland%29.svg.png
